Controls whether a view can take focus. By default, this is "auto" which lets the framework determine whether a user can move focus to a view. By setting this attribute to true the view is allowed to take focus. By setting it to "false" the view will not take focus. This value does not impact the behavior of directly calling {@link android.view.ViewrequestFocus}, which will always request focus regardless of this view. It only impacts where focus navigation will try to move focus.
